Note:
HIR to Elixir Generator - Generate idiomatic Elixir source from HIR.

This file consumes the hir.runa dictionary/list-literal HIR produced by
elixir_to_hir.runa (the model-3 interchange) and re-emits valid Elixir text. It
dispatches on the exact "_type" string tags the frontend emits: elixir_module,
function, clause, defstruct, defexception, module_attribute, alias, import,
require, use, defprotocol, defimpl, pipe, call, case, cond, with, with_clause,
if, unless, for, try, receive, match_clause, fn, capture, map, struct_literal,
pair, tuple, list, binary, identifier, alias_ref, atom, literal, binary_op,
unary_op, pin, access, keyword_pair, block.

It produces idiomatic Elixir: defmodule Name do ... end; def/defp name(params)
when guard do ... end; defstruct [a: 1, b: 2]; @attr value; alias/import/require/
use; a |> b |> c pipes; case expr do pattern -> body end; %{k => v} maps;
%Name{...} struct literals; fn args -> body end; for gen <- coll do body end.

Dependencies:
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/elixir/elixir_emitter.runa
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/elixir/elixir_emitter.runa" as Emitter
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListOps

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Generation Context
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The generator carries the emitter (backing byte buffer) and the current
indentation level. Elixir blocks are introduced by do ... end with 2-space
indentation; the level feeds emit_indent so every generator writes a single line.
@End Reasoning
Type called "HirToElixirContext":
    emitter as Integer          Note: Elixir emitter instance
    indent_level as Integer     Note: Current indentation level
End Type

@Reasoning:
Initialises the context at indent level 0 with the supplied emitter. Returns 0 on
allocation failure.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_to_elixir_context" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Let context be proc allocate from Layout with 16
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, emitter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 0
    Return context
End Process

@Reasoning:
Releases the context struct; the emitter is owned by the caller so the output
buffer survives.
@End Reasoning
Process called "destroy_hir_to_elixir_context" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with context
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Increases indentation by one level.
@End Reasoning
Process called "increase_indent" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, current plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Decreases indentation by one level, guarded against underflow so a malformed HIR
cannot drive indent_level negative.
@End Reasoning
Process called "decrease_indent" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8
    If current is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, current minus 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits the current indentation as spaces via the emitter.
@End Reasoning
Process called "emit_indent" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    Let level be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8
    proc emit_indent from Emitter with emitter, level
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Thin emitter wrappers so the generators read cleanly. Each forwards to the
emitter held in the context.
@End Reasoning
Process called "out_str" takes context as Integer, text as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, text
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "out_char" takes context as Integer, ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, ch
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "out_newline" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "out_space" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    proc emit_space from Emitter with emitter
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIR Decode Helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
hir.runa exposes dictionary contents only as an entries List of 16-byte
[key(0), value(8)] blocks via get_dictionary_entries; it has no keyed lookup.
This accessor performs the linear key scan the frontend's producer surface pairs
with, returning the matching entry's value node or 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_dictionary_value" takes dict_hir as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict_hir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with dict_hir
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from ListOps with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from ListOps with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a keyed value that is stored as a HIR string literal and unwraps it to
its char* payload. Returns 0 when absent.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_dict_string_value" takes dict_hir as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict_hir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc get_dictionary_value with dict_hir, key
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns a keyed subtree (dict or list HIR node) unmodified.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_dict_hir_value" takes dict_hir as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict_hir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_dictionary_value with dict_hir, key
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the backing element List of a HIR list-literal node so generators iterate
with size / get_at.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_elements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a node's "_type" string equals tag. Central type test.
@End Reasoning
Process called "type_is" takes node as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nt be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, tag
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry: pairs an emitter with a fresh context, drives the recursive walker
from the HIR root, and lifts the output string before destroying the context (the
emitter buffer outlives both). Returns 0 on null root.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_elixir_from_hir" takes hir_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate Elixir source text from HIR

    If hir_root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let emitter be proc create_elixir_emitter from Emitter
    If emitter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let context be proc create_hir_to_elixir_context with emitter
    If context is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_elixir_emitter from Emitter with emitter
        Return 0
    End If

    proc generate_node with context, hir_root

    Let output be proc get_output from Emitter with emitter

    proc destroy_hir_to_elixir_context with context
    proc destroy_elixir_emitter from Emitter with emitter

    Return output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Central dispatcher. Reads the "_type" tag and routes to the matching generator.
Module + declarations first, then control-flow expressions, then leaves; unknown
tags return 0 silently.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_node" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nt be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "elixir_module":
        Return proc generate_module with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "function":
        Return proc generate_function with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defstruct":
        Return proc generate_defstruct with context, node, "defstruct"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defexception":
        Return proc generate_defstruct with context, node, "defexception"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "module_attribute":
        Return proc generate_module_attribute with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "alias":
        Return proc generate_directive with context, node, "alias"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "import":
        Return proc generate_directive with context, node, "import"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "require":
        Return proc generate_directive with context, node, "require"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "use":
        Return proc generate_directive with context, node, "use"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defprotocol":
        Return proc generate_defprotocol with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defimpl":
        Return proc generate_defimpl with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "pipe":
        Return proc generate_pipe with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "call":
        Return proc generate_call with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "case":
        Return proc generate_case with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "cond":
        Return proc generate_cond with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "with":
        Return proc generate_with with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "with_clause":
        Return proc generate_with_clause with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "if":
        Return proc generate_if with context, node, "if"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "unless":
        Return proc generate_if with context, node, "unless"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "for":
        Return proc generate_for with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "try":
        Return proc generate_try with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "receive":
        Return proc generate_receive with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "match_clause":
        Return proc generate_match_clause with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "fn":
        Return proc generate_fn with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "capture":
        Return proc generate_capture with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "map":
        Return proc generate_map with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "struct_literal":
        Return proc generate_struct_literal with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "pair":
        Return proc generate_pair with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "tuple":
        Return proc generate_tuple with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "list":
        Return proc generate_list with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "binary":
        Return proc generate_binary with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "identifier":
        Return proc generate_identifier with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "alias_ref":
        Return proc generate_alias_ref with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "atom":
        Return proc generate_atom with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "literal":
        Return proc generate_literal with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "binary_op":
        Return proc generate_binary_op with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "unary_op":
        Return proc generate_unary_op with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "pin":
        Return proc generate_pin with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "access":
        Return proc generate_access with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "keyword_pair":
        Return proc generate_keyword_pair with context, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "block":
        Return proc generate_block with context, node
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Module + member generation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A module emits 'defmodule Name do\n  <members>\nend'. The body members are
emitted one per logical statement at one indentation level deeper, each on its
own line via generate_member_line. A blank module name (anonymous top-level
container) emits its members at top level without the defmodule wrapper.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_module" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "name"

    Let has_name be 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        Let name_len be proc string_length from StringCore with name
        If name_len is greater than 0:
            Set has_name to 1
        End If
    End If

    Let members be proc get_dict_hir_value with node, "members"

    If has_name is equal to 1:
        proc emit_indent with context
        proc out_str with context, "defmodule "
        proc out_str with context, name
        proc out_str with context, " do"
        proc out_newline with context
        proc increase_indent with context
        proc generate_member_list with context, members
        proc decrease_indent with context
        proc emit_indent with context
        proc out_str with context, "end"
        proc out_newline with context
    Otherwise:
        proc generate_member_list with context, members
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits every member in a HIR list as its own indented statement line. Each member
generator emits its own trailing newline, so members are line-separated.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_member_list" takes context as Integer, members as Integer returns Integer:
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc size from ListOps with items
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let member be proc get_at from ListOps with items, i
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_member_line with context, member
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one module member. Declaration members (function, defstruct, attributes,
directives, protocols, impls) already manage their own indentation + newline.
Bare expression members are emitted as an indented expression line.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_member_line" takes context as Integer, member as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nt be proc get_dict_string_value with member, "_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_decl be proc is_declaration_tag with nt
    If is_decl is equal to 1:
        proc generate_node with context, member
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: bare expression statement member
    proc emit_indent with context
    proc generate_node with context, member
    proc out_newline with context
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when the tag is a module-level declaration that self-manages indentation
and a trailing newline (so generate_member_line does not double-wrap it).
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_declaration_tag" takes nt as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "function":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defstruct":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defexception":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "module_attribute":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "alias":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "import":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "require":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "use":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defprotocol":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "defimpl":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "elixir_module":
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
A function emits one 'def'/'defp' head per clause: 'def name(params) when guard
do\n  body\nend'. The keyword (def vs defp) is taken from the "kind" attribute if
present, else derived from visibility. Every clause is emitted so multi-clause
functions reconstruct.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_function" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let kind be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "kind"
    Let keyword be proc resolve_def_keyword with node, kind
    Let name be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "name"

    Let clauses be proc get_dict_hir_value with node, "clauses"
    If clauses is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with clauses
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc size from ListOps with items
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let clause be proc get_at from ListOps with items, i
        If clause is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_function_clause with context, clause, keyword, name
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves the def keyword to emit. Uses the explicit "kind" attribute when it is
one of the recognised def forms; otherwise falls back to visibility ("private" ->
defp, anything else -> def).
@End Reasoning
Process called "resolve_def_keyword" takes node as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If kind is not equal to 0:
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "def":
            Return "def"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defp":
            Return "defp"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defmacro":
            Return "defmacro"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defmacrop":
            Return "defmacrop"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defguard":
            Return "defguard"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defguardp":
            Return "defguardp"
        End If
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "defdelegate":
            Return "defdelegate"
        End If
    End If

    Let visibility be proc get_dict_string_value with node, "visibility"
    If visibility is not equal to 0:
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "private":
            Return "defp"
        End If
    End If
    Return "def"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one clause head + body. 'keyword name(params)' then, if a guard is present,
' when guard', then ' do\n  body\nend'. params are comma-separated; the body
statements are emitted one per indented line.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_function_clause" takes context as Integer, clause as Integer, keyword as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emit_indent with context
    proc out_str with context, keyword
    proc out_space with context
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc out_str with context, name
    End If
    proc out_char with context, 40
    Let params be proc get_dict_hir_value with clause, "params"
    proc generate_expr_list with context, params
    proc out_char with context, 41

    Let guard be proc get_dict_hir_value with clause, "guard"
    If guard is not equal to 0:
        proc out_str with context, " when "
        proc generate_node with context, guard
    End If

    proc out_str with context, " do"
    proc out_newline with context

    proc increase_indent with context
    Let body be proc get_dict_hir_value with clause, "body"
    proc generate_statement_list with context, body
    proc decrease_indent with context

    proc emit_indent with context
    proc out_str with context, "end"
    proc out_newline with context
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A defstruct/defexception emits 'defstruct [field: default, field2: nil]'. The
keyword selects defstruct vs defexception. Each field is emitted from its pair.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_defstruct" takes context as Integer, node as Integer, keyword as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emit_indent with context
    proc out_str with context, keyword
    proc out_space with context
    proc out_char with context, 91

    Let fields be proc get_dict_hir_value with node, "fields"
    If fields is not equal to 0:
        Let items be proc list_elements with fields
        If items is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc size from ListOps with items
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than count:
                If i is greater than 0:
                    proc out_str with context, ", "
                End If
                Let pair be proc get_at from ListOps with items, i
                proc generate_struct_field with context, pair
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    proc out_char with context, 93
    proc out_newline with context
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one defstruct field. The key is a pair node whose "key" is an expression
(usually an atom) and whose "value" may be 0 (bare key) or a default expression.
A bare atom key 'foo' is emitted as 'foo: nil' (keyword-list form requires a
value), preserving the field name; a present value emits 'name: value'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_struct_field" takes context as Integer, pair as Integer returns Integer:
    Let key be proc get_dict_hir_value with pair, "key"
    Let value be proc get_dict_hir_value with pair, "value"

    Let field_name be proc field_key_name with key

    If field_name is not equal to 0:
        proc out_str with context, field_name
        proc out_str with context, ": "
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_node with context, value
        Otherwise:
            proc out_str with context, "nil"
        End If
    Otherwise:
        proc generate_node with context, key
        proc out_str with context, " => "
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_node with context, value
        Otherwise:
            proc out_str with context, "nil"
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Extracts the bare field name from a key node. An atom key value ":name" yields
"name" (the colon stripped); an identifier key yields its name. Returns 0 when the
key is not a simple name (caller falls back to the map-style form).
@End Reasoning
Process called "field_key_name" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_atom be proc type_is with key, "atom"
    If is_atom is equal to 1:
        Let value be proc get_dict_string_value with key, "value"
        If value is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc strip_leading_colon with value
    End If

    Let is_id be proc type_is with key, "identifier"
    If is_id is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_dict_string_value with key, "name"
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Strips a single leading ':' from an atom lexeme so ":name" becomes "name". When
the string has no leading colon it is returned unchanged.
@End Reasoning
Process called "strip_leading_colon" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with s
    If len is equal to 0:
        Return s
    End If
    Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with s, 0
    If first is equal to 58:
        Return proc string_substring from StringPrim with s, 1, len minus 1
    End If
    Return s
End Process

@Reasoning:
A module attribute emits '@name value' on its own line. A 0 value (bare @attr)
emits just '@name'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_module_attribute" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emit_indent with context
